    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>B</abbr><ex>onae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>emoriae</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>&amp;lt;D=O&amp;gt;esideria <note>sic</note> qu<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> visit <note>sic</note> in s<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>eculo</abbr></expan> <lb n="3"/>an<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>us</abbr></expan> <note>sic</note> plus <expan><abbr>minu</abbr><ex>s</ex></expan> XXVI fecit <lb n="4"/>qum <note>sic</note> Birginio <note>sic</note> suo annus <note>sic</note> XIII <lb n="5"/>deposita est VX <expan><abbr>K</abbr><ex>alendas</ex></expan> Febr<expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>arias</abbr></expan> 
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Z. 2: Opsideria - Epigraphica 1; Opsidiria - Studi; Z. 4: Birginio - Epigraphica 1; berginio - Studi, Epigraphica 41, AE; Z. 5: Februarias - Epigraphica 1. Birginius = Virginius möglicherweise kein Name, sondern eine Epitheton für Tugendhaftigkeit.</p>
            </div>
